main event: A resident in Baronette, Wisconsin reported seeing a flying object on January 25, 1953.
interesting points: The object was described as approximately 10 feet in diameter, white and blue in color.
The object appeared to be a rocket or jet, traveling at a very high speed.
The object made a sudden stop, then continued traveling at a high rate of speed and disappeared into a cloud.
The object had a bluish-green glow as it disappeared.
The sighting lasted for approximately 10 minutes.
result: Possibly an astronomical object, no specific identifying data was included.
sighted object: a flying object, described as a rocket or jet
